  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Brazil to Reduce the Risk of COVID-19 Spread and Increase Resilience of Vulnerable Brazilian Populations in Roraima and Amazonas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The rapid spread of the disease and the impact of the pandemic poses a major challenge for Brazil, particularly for its northern states, due to the lack of emergency care, inadequate health promotion measures and direct support to those in need. To support Brazil&#xB4;s preparedness to reduce the risk of COVID-19 and its impact on the vulnerable Brazilian populations living in two poorest northern states of Brazil, states of Roraima and Amazonas, this project aims to support existing health care facilities in remote areas and health professional, ensure provision of non-food items, water, sanitation, and hygiene services to implement preventive measures and support frontline personnel. The proposed project is in line with IOM&#xB4;s South America Regional COVID-19 Strategic Response Plan.</narrative>
  </description>
